        </section>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/customizing_ai_positron_for_your_dita_xml_project.dita" xtrc="p:2;22:12">With their ability to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/customizing_ai_positron_for_your_dita_xml_project.dita" xtrc="b:7;22:37">rewrite</b>, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/customizing_ai_positron_for_your_dita_xml_project.dita" xtrc="b:8;22:53">research</b>, and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/customizing_ai_positron_for_your_dita_xml_project.dita" xtrc="b:9;22:74">generate documentation
                drafts</b> AI models can be useful in a variety of cases as long as aspects specific
            to the current DITA XML project can be controlled and enforced.</p>
